item.title: Port Fowarding [NETGEAR]
item.dc:creator: @alvin alvin
item.description:
@alvin wrote:

[quote=“I r Pwn u, post:8, topic:446838”][quote author=alvin link=topic=549718.msg4029519#msg4029519 date=1340626308]

If you’re using a modem the port should automatically be open, on the other hand if you’re using a router you can just go to the default gateway which is 192.168.1.1 for almost everyone and go to Portfowarding/triggering and you can open the 43594 port easily. There’s several tutorials you can use, but I just explained it the short way.

To be honest I tried everything(or so I think everything). My router model is CGD24G, I’ve gone to websites and I’ve read the tutorials they have on here, nothing seems to help. Let me show you what I have going.

That’s what I have setup and it doesn’t work . . .

Are you sure that’s the correct ending local ip address? It may not be .99, that could be the problem. I’ve dealt with this several times.

No I’m not sure, how do I make sure lol.

Run CMD and enter “ipconfig” there should be a list of IP’s, the one that’s 192.168.1.xx should be the correct one, not the default gateway.

Ipv4 address right -___- omg if this fixes this I will officially feel retarded
[/quote]

Try that and see if it works, I’m not fluent with Routers anymore since I haven’t portforwarded in over a year but that’s my best advice for now.[/quote]

Still get the same error from original post :\

Read full topic
